notesStmt.note: Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.summary: The Prophets and Hagiographa with masorah magna and parva.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 2; ruled lines: 30; written lines: 30; Uniform layout. Pricking (occasionally) and complete hard-point ruling visible. Hair side and flesh side of folios distinguishable. Beginning of a weekly section marked by the word סדר in the margin. The sign פפ stands between the sections. Masorah magna is written in two lines in the upper margin and in three lines in the lower margin.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Sefardi square script of the 14th century, punctuated and accentuated.

binding.p: BM/BL in-house. Spine: 'The Prophets and Hagiographa. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Oriental 6570.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Acquired by the British Museum from M. Dahan on 12 March 1904.
